author: @BlitzIn4
comment: 23:56 He is incorrect. When the moving scrollable content is moving up, you are scrolling down. He could be scrolling right on his screen and if the content is disappearing at the top and new content is appearing at the bottom, he would then be scrolling down, not scrolling right. In the future when we are all using Google Lens and we don't use touch screens but instead use our eyes to move down a page, are we to call it 'look down' to scroll down the page? No, it will still be called scroll down. What about people who use Google Lens and people who use smart phones and people who use a playstation controller, they need the same terminology to communicate with each other. There is only one correct term. It is scroll down.
